    "For example, a student's current academic performance is influenced by complex interactions between different factors, such as socio-economic background and prior academic performance as in Yousafzai et al (2021) where it has achieved 90.16% prediction accuracy.",
    "Hybrid Deep Learning models combine multiple neural network architectures to predict student performance effectively.",
    "These models can leverage the strengths of different architectures and combine them to improve overall performance Towell and Shavlik (1994).",
    "One of the most commonly used hybrid DL models for predicting student performance is the combination of CNN with RNN, such as LSTM or GRU, which takes the strengths of both architectures and improves the prediction accuracy.",
    "In terms of the model architecture, the CNN-LSTM hybrid model is flexible in terms of the number of CNN and LSTM layers adjusted in accordance with the difficulty of the problem statement and input data."
